<Issue id="30141" key="FABG-403" number="403" project="10610" reporter="ga25waq" assignee="aleksandar.likic" creator="ga25waq" type="10004" summary="MSP client provokes nil pointer panic for non-existent organizations" priority="2" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2018-05-11 16:26:34.0" updated="2018-07-18 23:52:44.0" resolutiondate="2018-05-11 20:37:36.0" votes="0" watches="1" workflowId="33202"> <description><! CDATA The new MSP client provokes a nil pointer panic if a non-existent/non-retrievable organization is handed over, e.g.  {code:java} mspClient, err := mspclient.New(sdk.Context(), mspclient.WithOrg("nonExistentOrg")) {code}  The _New_ method neither returns a nil pointer nor an error. Subsequently, the following error occurs when calling _mspClient.GetSigningIdentity_:  {code:java} panic: runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference  signal SIGSEGV: segmentation violation code=0x1 addr=0x20 pc=0xa63a73   goroutine 1  running : github.com/hyperledger/fabric-sdk-go/pkg/client/msp.(*Client).GetSigningIdentity(0xc42029b2a0, 0xc42001206f, 0x5, 0x1, 0xc42029b2a0, 0x0, 0x0) /opt/gopath/src/github.com/hyperledger/fabric-sdk-go/pkg/client/msp/client.go:410 +0x53 {code}  ></description> </Issue>
